results.lead_paragraph: Jim Carrey removes a check for $10 million from his wallet. It says: "For acting services rendered by Thanksgiving, 1995." It's a joke, of course. The star of the weekend's No. 1 film, "The Mask," wrote it to himself years ago when he was unknown, barely eking out a living and seized with fantasies of earning a ton of money.

headline.main: Astronaut Lands at Museum, Leaving Children Starry-Eyed

results.snippet: AS densely packed as stars in the Milky Way, a line of autograph seekers cut a wide swath across the courtyard of the Hudson River Museum here one recent afternoon, as hundreds waited in the heat to shake the freckled hand of an astronaut, Charles...
results.lead_paragraph: AS densely packed as stars in the Milky Way, a line of autograph seekers cut a wide swath across the courtyard of the Hudson River Museum here one recent afternoon, as hundreds waited in the heat to shake the freckled hand of an astronaut, Charles E. Brady. The occasion, called Astronaut Training Day at the museum, marked the 25th anniversary of two events: the landing of American astronauts on the moon and the opening of the museum's Andrus Planetarium.

headline.main: Space Shuttle Is Set For Ecological Study

results.snippet: For the second time in four months, a space shuttle was poised yesterday to carry powerful radar instruments into orbit. The astronauts plan to survey Earth's delicate environments and help map an ancient Arabian city.   The Endeavour is ready to...
results.lead_paragraph: For the second time in four months, a space shuttle was poised yesterday to carry powerful radar instruments into orbit. The astronauts plan to survey Earth's delicate environments and help map an ancient Arabian city. The Endeavour is ready to carry out the second Space Radar Laboratory mission and is scheduled to be launched at 6:54 A.M. on Thursday from the Kennedy Space Center. The six crew members arrived yesterday at the launching site, and the National Aeronautics and Space Administration began a three-day countdown at 11 A.M. Storms approaching from the Gulf of Mexico and the Bahamas may delay the launching.

headline.main: 2 Aliens (American Variety) Train for Russian Space Mission

results.snippet: Four floors above the apartment where Yuri Gagarin lived after his pioneer space flight in 1961, an American astronaut sat down to dinner recently with Russian teachers.   It had been a long day for the astronaut, Norman Thagard, starting with a...
results.lead_paragraph: Four floors above the apartment where Yuri Gagarin lived after his pioneer space flight in 1961, an American astronaut sat down to dinner recently with Russian teachers. It had been a long day for the astronaut, Norman Thagard, starting with a lecture on the Russian space station, Mir, and ending with four hours of basic Russian.
